column5: got out tonight for some evening/night trolling...  and what a night...  in about 3 hours we went 22 for 23... i say WE but my buddy would argue... i think he only got 4-5 of them...lol... same lure...  they were hitting very light for the most part... most were hooked with one barb on the back treble... but thats all i needed...  most fish were 3-5 pounds...  but one...  i got a 28 incher that weighed 9.2 lbs... talk about fat!!!
I've never seen an obese walleye before.  Two thumbs up!
Man !!! Thats some porker Bud !!!! Beautiful color this time of year.Almost gold
you are not really making this easy for me to keep my fishing stuff stored till spring!!!  :thumbsup_anim:
Awesome, that's a nice fat walleye.  Great specimen!!
nice !!!! that big eye is eating well...
It was pretty chilly...  Our rod guides were freezing and my boat carpet had a nice layer of ice on it at the end...

wow thats wicked! awesome job mike. and you got a good picture to boot. hahah just teasing ya man.  im starting to itch a bit for some big eyes. last trip to quinte is booked for dec 8-12, im sure it will be a cold one.  thanks for sharing. cheers
Gorgeous Walleye....can't help but notice that it looks totally ashamed of itself  :lol:
Hardcore man--nice fish to be sure. Good dining that night I take it???
That is sweet. Way to go.
Nice night,man -- what time did you fish from/to?
